docs.title: API Reference
docs.description: This section provides comprehensive documentation for the humanoid robotics APIs, libraries, and interfaces used in the implementation of humanoid robots. The reference materials cover core control interfaces, sensor APIs, communication protocols, and utility functions.

docs.title: Code Examples
docs.description: This section provides practical code examples for implementing humanoid robotics concepts. The examples cover control systems, sensor integration, AI algorithms, and complete implementation patterns.

docs.title: Hardware Specifications
docs.description: This section provides detailed technical specifications for humanoid robot hardware components, including actuators, sensors, computational systems, and mechanical designs.

docs.title: Basic Control Examples
docs.description: This section provides fundamental control examples for humanoid robotics, covering essential concepts like joint control, balance maintenance, and basic locomotion patterns.

docs.title: Deployment Guides
docs.description: This section provides detailed guides for deploying humanoid robots in various environments and applications. The guides cover safety procedures, system integration, maintenance protocols, and operational best practices.

docs.title: Simulation Workflows
docs.description: This section provides comprehensive tutorials on setting up, configuring, and running humanoid robot simulations. The workflows cover various simulation platforms, sensor integration, control system testing, and validation procedures.
